juniPppoeAgent.name: juniPppoeAgent

revisions.description: Added unknownAction configuration support in PPPoE service name table
Added Interface Lockout configuration and state support.
Added PADR Remote Circuit Id Capture support.
Replaced invalid session counter with separate PADI and PADR invalid session counters. Added invalid length and invalid tag length counters. Added ServiceName table support.
Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names.
Added AC-NAME and duplicate MAC address indicator objects.
The initial release of this management information module.

juniPppoeAgent.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 E-mail: mib@Juniper.net
juniPppoeAgent.description: The agent capabilities definitions for the point-to-point protocol over Ethernet (PPPoE) component of the SNMP agent in JUNOSe family of products.

juniPppoeAgentV1.name: juniPppoeAgentV1
juniPppoeAgentV1.productrelease:
Version 1 of the PPPoE component of the JUNOSe SNMP agent.  This
        version of the PPPoE component was supported in JUNOSe 3.0 thru 3.2.2
        system releases.
juniPppoeAgentV1.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the PPPoE application in JUNOSe. These capabilities became obsolete when AC-NAME and duplicate MAC address indicator objects were added.

juniPppoeAgentV2.name: juniPppoeAgentV2
juniPppoeAgentV2.productrelease:
Version 2 of the PPPoE component of the JUNOSe SNMP agent.  This
        version of the PPPoE component was supported in JUNOSe 3.2.3 through 3.x
        system releases.
juniPppoeAgentV2.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the PPPoE application in JUNOSe. These capabilities became obsolete when PADI flag support was added.

juniPppoeAgentV3.name: juniPppoeAgentV3
juniPppoeAgentV3.productrelease:
Version 3 of the PPPoE component of the JUNOSe SNMP agent.  This
        version of the PPPoE component was supported in JUNOSe 4.0 system
        releases.
juniPppoeAgentV3.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the PPPoE application in the JUNOSe. These capabilities became obsolete when PADN counter support was added.

juniPppoeAgentV4.name: juniPppoeAgentV4
juniPppoeAgentV4.productrelease:
Version 4 of the PPPoE component of the JUNOSe SNMP agent.  This
        version of the PPPoE component was supported in JUNOSe 4.1 through 5.0
        system releases.
juniPppoeAgentV4.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the PPPoE application in JUNOSe. These capabilities became obsolete when the invalid session counter was replaced by separate PADI and PADR invalid session counters, invalid length and invalid tag length counters and service name table support were added.

juniPppoeAgentV5.name: juniPppoeAgentV5

juniPppoeAgentV5.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the PPPoE application in JUNOSe. These capabilities became obsolete when PADR remote-circuit-id field was added.

juniPppoeAgentV6.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the PPPoE application in JUNOSe. These capabilities became obsolete when MTU configuration was added.

juniPppoeAgentV7.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the PPPoE application in JUNOSe. These capabilities became obsolete when lockout configuration was added.
